text: Stonehenge is a locality in the Toowoomba Region, Queensland, Australia. ==History== The locality was named after a relatively small pastoral run established by Herbert Evans in the 1840s. The name relates to rock formations near the homestead. Stonehenge was opened for selection on 17 April 1877; were available. ==References== Category:Toowoomba Region Category:Localities in Queensland
title: Stonehenge, Queensland (Toowoomba Region)
